{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":803,"text":"So little Billy goes to school,"},{"time":3587,"text":"and he sits down and the teacher says,"},{"time":6344,"text":"\"What does your father do?\""},{"time":9349,"text":"And little Billy says, \"My father plays the piano"},{"time":13006,"text":"in an opium den.\""},{"time":16112,"text":"So the teacher rings up the parents, and says,"},{"time":18101,"text":"\"Very shocking story from little Billy today."},{"time":21355,"text":"Just heard that he claimed that you play the piano"},{"time":25104,"text":"in an opium den.\""},{"time":27264,"text":"And the father says, \"I'm very sorry. Yes, it's true, I lied."},{"time":31123,"text":"But how can I tell an eight-year-old boy"},{"time":34754,"text":"that his father is a politician?\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":39163,"text":"Now, as a politician myself, standing in front of you,"},{"time":42411,"text":"or indeed, meeting any stranger anywhere in the world,"},{"time":46066,"text":"when I eventually reveal the nature of my profession,"},{"time":48642,"text":"they look at me as though I'm somewhere between"},{"time":51736,"text":"a snake, a monkey and an iguana,"},{"time":56490,"text":"and through all of this, I feel, strongly,"},{"time":60432,"text":"that something is going wrong."},{"time":63414,"text":"Four hundred years of maturing democracy,"},{"time":66610,"text":"colleagues in Parliament who seem to me, as individuals,"},{"time":69478,"text":"reasonably impressive, an increasingly educated,"},{"time":73056,"text":"energetic, informed population, and yet"},{"time":77703,"text":"a deep, deep sense of disappointment."},{"time":82607,"text":"My colleagues in Parliament include, in my new intake,"},{"time":86579,"text":"family doctors, businesspeople, professors,"},{"time":91333,"text":"distinguished economists, historians, writers,"},{"time":95556,"text":"army officers ranging from colonels down to regimental sergeant majors."},{"time":100558,"text":"All of them, however, including myself, as we walk underneath"},{"time":104219,"text":"those strange stone gargoyles just down the road,"},{"time":108327,"text":"feel that we've become less than the sum of our parts,"},{"time":112353,"text":"feel as though we have become profoundly diminished."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118026,"text":"And this isn't just a problem in Britain."},{"time":122154,"text":"It's a problem across the developing world,"},{"time":124887,"text":"and in middle income countries too. In Jamaica,"},{"time":127521,"text":"for example -- look at Jamaican members of Parliament,"},{"time":130829,"text":"you meet them, and they're often people who are"},{"time":133809,"text":"Rhodes Scholars, who've studied at Harvard or at Princeton,"},{"time":139253,"text":"and yet, you go down to downtown Kingston,"},{"time":142314,"text":"and you are looking at one of the most depressing sites"},{"time":145958,"text":"that you can see in any middle-income country in the world:"},{"time":150043,"text":"a dismal, depressing landscape"},{"time":152806,"text":"of burnt and half-abandoned buildings."},{"time":155996,"text":"And this has been true for 30 years, and the handover"},{"time":159124,"text":"in 1979, 1980, between one Jamaican leader who was"},{"time":163390,"text":"the son of a Rhodes Scholar and a Q.C. to another"},{"time":166865,"text":"who'd done an economics doctorate at Harvard,"},{"time":170095,"text":"over 800 people were killed in the streets"},{"time":173098,"text":"in drug-related violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176625,"text":"Ten years ago, however, the promise of democracy"},{"time":180107,"text":"seemed to be extraordinary. George W. Bush stood up"},{"time":184090,"text":"in his State of the Union address in 2003"},{"time":187250,"text":"and said that democracy was the force that would beat"},{"time":191279,"text":"most of the ills of the world. He said,"},{"time":194305,"text":"because democratic governments respect their own people"},{"time":198078,"text":"and respect their neighbors, freedom will bring peace."},{"time":203812,"text":"Distinguished academics at the same time argued that"},{"time":207446,"text":"democracies had this incredible range of side benefits."},{"time":211124,"text":"They would bring prosperity, security,"},{"time":214424,"text":"overcome sectarian violence,"},{"time":217245,"text":"ensure that states would never again harbor terrorists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221710,"text":"Since then, what's happened?"},{"time":224064,"text":"Well, what we've seen is the creation, in places like Iraq"},{"time":227258,"text":"and Afghanistan, of democratic systems of government"},{"time":231246,"text":"which haven't had any of those side benefits."},{"time":234136,"text":"In Afghanistan, for example, we haven't just had one election"},{"time":237129,"text":"or two elections. We've gone through three elections,"},{"time":239796,"text":"presidential and parliamentary. And what do we find?"},{"time":242923,"text":"Do we find a flourishing civil society, a vigorous rule of law"},{"time":246534,"text":"and good security? No. What we find in Afghanistan"},{"time":249995,"text":"is a judiciary that is weak and corrupt,"},{"time":254140,"text":"a very limited civil society which is largely ineffective,"},{"time":258325,"text":"a media which is beginning to get onto its feet"},{"time":261329,"text":"but a government that's deeply unpopular,"},{"time":264154,"text":"perceived as being deeply corrupt, and security"},{"time":267922,"text":"that is shocking, security that's terrible."},{"time":271735,"text":"In Pakistan, in lots of sub-Saharan Africa,"},{"time":276393,"text":"again you can see democracy and elections are compatible"},{"time":279385,"text":"with corrupt governments, with states that are unstable"},{"time":283234,"text":"and dangerous."},{"time":286091,"text":"And when I have conversations with people, I remember"},{"time":288375,"text":"having a conversation, for example, in Iraq,"},{"time":291256,"text":"with a community that asked me"},{"time":293945,"text":"whether the riot we were seeing in front of us,"},{"time":297455,"text":"this was a huge mob ransacking a provincial council building,"},{"time":301278,"text":"was a sign of the new democracy."},{"time":305970,"text":"The same, I felt, was true in almost every single one"},{"time":310111,"text":"of the middle and developing countries that I went to,"},{"time":313059,"text":"and to some extent the same is true of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317110,"text":"Well, what is the answer to this? Is the answer to just"},{"time":319686,"text":"give up on the idea of democracy?"},{"time":322344,"text":"Well, obviously not. It would be absurd"},{"time":326086,"text":"if we were to engage again in the kind of operations"},{"time":328873,"text":"we were engaged in, in Iraq and Afghanistan"},{"time":331949,"text":"if we were to suddenly find ourselves in a situation"},{"time":335469,"text":"in which we were imposing"},{"time":338144,"text":"anything other than a democratic system."},{"time":340583,"text":"Anything else would run contrary to our values,"},{"time":343135,"text":"it would run contrary to the wishes of the people"},{"time":345386,"text":"on the ground, it would run contrary to our interests."},{"time":349009,"text":"I remember in Iraq, for example, that we went through"},{"time":352316,"text":"a period of feeling that we should delay democracy."},{"time":354857,"text":"We went through a period of feeling that the lesson learned"},{"time":357549,"text":"from Bosnia was that elections held too early"},{"time":361127,"text":"enshrined sectarian violence, enshrined extremist parties,"},{"time":365361,"text":"so in Iraq in 2003 the decision was made,"},{"time":368179,"text":"let's not have elections for two years. Let's invest in"},{"time":371296,"text":"voter education. Let's invest in democratization."},{"time":375468,"text":"The result was that I found stuck outside my office"},{"time":379486,"text":"a huge crowd of people, this is actually a photograph"},{"time":381658,"text":"taken in Libya but I saw the same scene in Iraq"},{"time":385138,"text":"of people standing outside screaming for the elections,"},{"time":389263,"text":"and when I went out and said, \"What is wrong"},{"time":392029,"text":"with the interim provincial council?"},{"time":394989,"text":"What is wrong with the people that we have chosen?"},{"time":398657,"text":"There is a Sunni sheikh, there's a Shiite sheikh,"},{"time":401402,"text":"there's the seven -- leaders of the seven major tribes,"},{"time":404553,"text":"there's a Christian, there's a Sabian,"},{"time":407107,"text":"there are female representatives, there's every political party in this council,"},{"time":411351,"text":"what's wrong with the people that we chose?\""},{"time":413991,"text":"The answer came, \"The problem isn't the people"},{"time":417089,"text":"that you chose. The problem is that you chose them.\""},{"time":422890,"text":"I have not met, in Afghanistan, in even the most"},{"time":426322,"text":"remote community, anybody who does not want"},{"time":429449,"text":"a say in who governs them."},{"time":432233,"text":"Most remote community, I have never met a villager"},{"time":434294,"text":"who does not want a vote."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437876,"text":"So we need to acknowledge"},{"time":441156,"text":"that despite the dubious statistics, despite the fact that"},{"time":444738,"text":"84 percent of people in Britain feel politics is broken,"},{"time":450161,"text":"despite the fact that when I was in Iraq, we did an opinion poll"},{"time":453133,"text":"in 2003 and asked people what political systems they preferred,"},{"time":457391,"text":"and the answer came back that"},{"time":459715,"text":"seven percent wanted the United States,"},{"time":462776,"text":"five percent wanted France,"},{"time":465499,"text":"three percent wanted Britain,"},{"time":468154,"text":"and nearly 40 percent wanted Dubai, which is, after all,"},{"time":472509,"text":"not a democratic state at all but a relatively prosperous"},{"time":475275,"text":"minor monarchy, democracy is a thing of value"},{"time":479978,"text":"for which we should be fighting. But in order to do so"},{"time":483140,"text":"we need to get away from instrumental arguments."},{"time":486492,"text":"We need to get away from saying democracy matters"},{"time":490060,"text":"because of the other things it brings."},{"time":493167,"text":"We need to get away from feeling, in the same way,"},{"time":495292,"text":"human rights matters because of the other things it brings,"},{"time":498889,"text":"or women's rights matters for the other things it brings."},{"time":502581,"text":"Why should we get away from those arguments?"},{"time":504885,"text":"Because they're very dangerous. If we set about saying,"},{"time":507289,"text":"for example, torture is wrong because it doesn't extract"},{"time":511982,"text":"good information, or we say, you need women's rights"},{"time":517180,"text":"because it stimulates economic growth by doubling the size of the work force,"},{"time":521860,"text":"you leave yourself open to the position where"},{"time":523517,"text":"the government of North Korea can turn around and say,"},{"time":525610,"text":"\"Well actually, we're having a lot of success extracting"},{"time":528473,"text":"good information with our torture at the moment,\""},{"time":530974,"text":"or the government of Saudi Arabia to say, \"Well,"},{"time":532934,"text":"our economic growth's okay, thank you very much,"},{"time":534663,"text":"considerably better than yours,"},{"time":536123,"text":"so maybe we don't need to go ahead with this program on women's rights.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":540929,"text":"The point about democracy is not instrumental."},{"time":544610,"text":"It's not about the things that it brings."},{"time":547399,"text":"The point about democracy is not that it delivers"},{"time":549964,"text":"legitimate, effective, prosperous rule of law."},{"time":556208,"text":"It's not that it guarantees peace with itself or with its neighbors."},{"time":560853,"text":"The point about democracy is intrinsic."},{"time":563770,"text":"Democracy matters because it reflects an idea of equality"},{"time":569101,"text":"and an idea of liberty. It reflects an idea of dignity,"},{"time":573509,"text":"the dignity of the individual, the idea that each individual"},{"time":577379,"text":"should have an equal vote, an equal say,"},{"time":580980,"text":"in the formation of their government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584975,"text":"But if we're really to make democracy vigorous again,"},{"time":589041,"text":"if we're ready to revivify it, we need to get involved"},{"time":591654,"text":"in a new project of the citizens and the politicians."},{"time":596455,"text":"Democracy is not simply a question of structures."},{"time":600843,"text":"It is a state of mind. It is an activity."},{"time":604860,"text":"And part of that activity is honesty."},{"time":608651,"text":"After I speak to you today, I'm going on a radio program"},{"time":612189,"text":"called \"Any Questions,\" and the thing you will have noticed"},{"time":614492,"text":"about politicians on these kinds of radio programs"},{"time":618292,"text":"is that they never, ever say that they don't know the answer"},{"time":621757,"text":"to a question. It doesn't matter what it is."},{"time":623392,"text":"If you ask about child tax credits, the future of the penguins"},{"time":626744,"text":"in the south Antarctic, asked to hold forth on whether or not"},{"time":631366,"text":"the developments in Chongqing contribute"},{"time":633998,"text":"to sustainable development in carbon capture,"},{"time":636332,"text":"and we will have an answer for you."},{"time":639094,"text":"We need to stop that, to stop pretending to be"},{"time":642279,"text":"omniscient beings."},{"time":644164,"text":"Politicians also need to learn, occasionally, to say that"},{"time":647724,"text":"certain things that voters want, certain things that voters"},{"time":651470,"text":"have been promised, may be things"},{"time":655333,"text":"that we cannot deliver"},{"time":658478,"text":"or perhaps that we feel we should not deliver."}]},{"cues":[{"time":662260,"text":"And the second thing we should do is understand"},{"time":665151,"text":"the genius of our societies."},{"time":668143,"text":"Our societies have never been so educated, have never"},{"time":672172,"text":"been so energized, have never been so healthy,"},{"time":675108,"text":"have never known so much, cared so much,"},{"time":678056,"text":"or wanted to do so much, and it is a genius of the local."},{"time":683952,"text":"One of the reasons why we're moving away"},{"time":686650,"text":"from banqueting halls such as the one in which we stand,"},{"time":690151,"text":"banqueting halls with extraordinary images on the ceiling"},{"time":694627,"text":"of kings enthroned,"},{"time":696402,"text":"the entire drama played out here on this space,"},{"time":699554,"text":"where the King of England had his head lopped off,"},{"time":702413,"text":"why we've moved from spaces like this, thrones like that,"},{"time":706744,"text":"towards the town hall, is we're moving more and more"},{"time":710469,"text":"towards the energies of our people, and we need to tap that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714417,"text":"That can mean different things in different countries."},{"time":717207,"text":"In Britain, it could mean looking to the French,"},{"time":720520,"text":"learning from the French,"},{"time":722263,"text":"getting directly elected mayors in place"},{"time":725892,"text":"in a French commune system."},{"time":728380,"text":"In Afghanistan, it could have meant instead of concentrating"},{"time":731214,"text":"on the big presidential and parliamentary elections,"},{"time":733768,"text":"we should have done what was in the Afghan constitution"},{"time":736085,"text":"from the very beginning, which is to get direct local elections going"},{"time":740765,"text":"at a district level and elect people's provincial governors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746312,"text":"But for any of these things to work,"},{"time":749035,"text":"the honesty in language, the local democracy,"},{"time":751858,"text":"it's not just a question of what politicians do."},{"time":754626,"text":"It's a question of what the citizens do."},{"time":756694,"text":"For politicians to be honest, the public needs to allow them to be honest,"},{"time":761601,"text":"and the media, which mediates between the politicians"},{"time":764180,"text":"and the public, needs to allow those politicians to be honest."},{"time":768811,"text":"If local democracy is to flourish, it is about the active"},{"time":772433,"text":"and informed engagement of every citizen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":776669,"text":"In other words, if democracy is to be rebuilt,"},{"time":781070,"text":"is to become again vigorous and vibrant,"},{"time":785394,"text":"it is necessary not just for the public"},{"time":788540,"text":"to learn to trust their politicians,"},{"time":791454,"text":"but for the politicians to learn to trust the public."},{"time":796326,"text":"Thank you very much indeed. (Applause)"}]}]}